    contentOn: 'A crisis in a relationship - after the birth of a child, loss of a job, illness - is not a failure. This is a phase that couples go through.\n\nDon\'t run away. A crisis is a signal that something needs attention—not that the relationship is over. Many couples emerge from the crisis stronger.\n\nSeek support. Therapy, conversations with friends, time for regeneration. You don\'t have to cope alone.\n\nArguments in a crisis are normal - the pressure is greater. The key is not giving up and saying "we are in this together".',
    contentOna: 'A crisis in a relationship is not the end - it is a phase. After a child, the loss of a job, an illness - many couples go through difficult times.\n\nDon\'t run away from difficulties. A crisis signals that something needs attention—not that love has disappeared. Many couples emerge stronger.\n\nSeek support. Therapy, conversations, time for yourself. You don\'t have to cope alone.\n\nArguments in a crisis are normal - the pressure is greater. "We are in this together" is the most important phrase in difficult times.',
