    contentOn: 'Gratitude is not a "thank you" said automatically. It is consciously noticing what your partner gives to the relationship.\n\nOne thing every day: what are you grateful for? Her patience? Cooking? Smile? Say it straight.\n\nGratitude changes your perspective. Instead of focusing on what is missing, you see what is there.\n\nPracticing gratitude strengthens your relationship. A partner who feels appreciated is more willing to give of herself - and this builds a positive cycle that will survive difficult times.',
